race.comment: TIGGERLONG GILL (2) comes here following a placing in handy time (18.24) over 320m at this track when beaten 3.5 lengths in a Free For All. Expected to push the clock again here. PERFECT LIAM (1) struggled in tougher grade last start after settling off pace at Nowra, but prior to that won by 1.5 lengths at this track (18.87) beating Paw Lilibet in a Grade 5 on October 24. Has the ability to give this a shake. TINY BIANCA (3) has been a little hard to follow, missing the frame last time but was a Grade 4/5 winner three starts ago and has drawn 3 where she has two wins. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Rates a winning chance on best. TALAKAI (4) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.
